elements.2211.03541_992e2f112669a6377df1b3876ca90: Efficient batched inference for multi-blank transducers
elements.2211.03541_17414cae50e0543875f3fcae31195: The multi-blank RNN-T method is ideal for on-device speech recognition in that it brings significant speedup in recognition speed as well as better accuracy
elements.2211.03541_72389a59c046decc26dd2fc91ad87: With that being said, the method also supports batched inference to run on the server side
elements.2211.03541_1bd72cb308f07a98175ea805ed53c: , we mentioned that during inference, when a big blank symbol is emitted, it should advance the input
elements.2211.03541_219ccc8a46e6a058f2ad36e09d92f: by the duration corresponding to the big blank
elements.2211.03541_83d0c60c5e5f12bd05fa67534d034: This makes it non-trivial to implement exact batched inference for multi-blank RNN-Ts, since different utterances in the same batch might output blanks with different durations, making it hard to fully parallelize the computation.
elements.2211.03541_633c14c71d0f0e490d3ee4944a100: batched inference method: if different utterances in a batch emit blanks of different durations, we increment
elements.2211.03541_bd76495e94e0bb651cbf5a0ce5ffb: by the minimum of those durations, e.g. if at frame
elements.2211.03541_78d64e6733643a0bba1e9487c15e2: , different utterances emit blanks of durations 1, 2, and 4, then the
elements.2211.03541_9d502bd80fb1d3f73afa6d193163a: is incremented by 1 for the next step in the batched decoding
elements.2211.03541_259a4f014f715bcb2aa7c014864a1: This allows for better parallelization for different utterances in the same batch
